From: "Rob Herring (Arm)" <robh@kernel.org>
Date: Tue, 18 Feb 2025 14:40:00 -0600
Subject: perf: arm_v7_pmu: Don't disable counter in
 (armv7|krait_|scorpion_)pmu_enable_event()
Git-commit: 7bf1001e0d9124ad65642a5bbff76b46a35798f3
Patch-mainline: v6.15-rc1
References: jsc#PED-15733 jsc#PED-15734

Currently (armv7|krait_|scorpion_)pmu_enable_event() start by disabling
the event counter it has been asked to enable. This should not be
necessary as the counter (and the PMU as a whole) should not be active
when *_enable_event() is called.

Signed-off-by: Rob Herring (Arm) <robh@kernel.org>
Reviewed-by: Anshuman Khandual <anshuman.khandual@arm.com>
Tested-by: James Clark <james.clark@linaro.org>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20250218-arm-brbe-v19-v20-5-4e9922fc2e8e@kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Will Deacon <will@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Stanimir Varbanov <svarbanov@suse.de>
---
 drivers/perf/arm_v7_pmu.c |    6 ------
 1 file changed, 6 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/perf/arm_v7_pmu.c
+++ b/drivers/perf/arm_v7_pmu.c
@@ -857,8 +857,6 @@ static void armv7pmu_enable_event(struct
 		return;
 	}
 
-	armv7_pmnc_disable_counter(idx);
-
 	/*
 	 * Set event (if destined for PMNx counters)
 	 * We only need to set the event for the cycle counter if we
@@ -1450,8 +1448,6 @@ static void krait_pmu_enable_event(struc
 	struct hw_perf_event *hwc = &event->hw;
 	int idx = hwc->idx;
 
-	armv7_pmnc_disable_counter(idx);
-
 	/*
 	 * Set event (if destined for PMNx counters)
 	 * We set the event for the cycle counter because we
@@ -1762,8 +1758,6 @@ static void scorpion_pmu_enable_event(st
 	struct hw_perf_event *hwc = &event->hw;
 	int idx = hwc->idx;
 
-	armv7_pmnc_disable_counter(idx);
-
 	/*
 	 * Set event (if destined for PMNx counters)
 	 * We don't set the event for the cycle counter because we
